# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: UnionKingdom | Scene: UnionKingdom8
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah had woken early the next day and had begun preparing."
    new "Sarah had woken early the next day and had begun preparing."

    old "Getting dressed, fixing her hair, studying the background documents of the other members of the council."
    new "Getting dressed, fixing her hair, studying the background documents of the other members of the council."

    old "Despite all of it, when Sarah arrived later that day at the council room, she felt unprepare still."
    new "Despite all of it, when Sarah arrived later that day at the council room, she felt unprepare still."

    old "Perhaps nothing could prepare her."
    new "Perhaps nothing could prepare her."

    old "The room itself was small, almost understated."
    new "The room itself was small, almost understated."

    old "Had she not been escorted there, she might have confused it for any other room."
    new "Had she not been escorted there, she might have confused it for any other room."

    old "But Sarah could understand why this served as their meeting room."
    new "But Sarah could understand why this served as their meeting room."

    old "The room sat in the deep heart of the castle. No windows, and only one door in and out."
    new "The room sat in the deep heart of the castle. No windows, and only one door in and out."

    old "It was exactly the kind of room that was build to keep in secrets."
    new "It was exactly the kind of room that was build to keep in secrets."

    old "She noticed Duke Antonio and Marshal Edmond were already seated."
    new "She noticed Duke Antonio and Marshal Edmond were already seated."

    old "You should have seen her, Edmond."
    new "You should have seen her, Edmond."

    old "Yes, I'm sure that-"
    new "Yes, I'm sure that-"

    old "No, I mean, this girl did things I've never seen before."
    new "No, I mean, this girl did things I've never seen before."

    old "And how she used her mouth, by the Gods I swear she must have studied in a Mythran brothel."
    new "And how she used her mouth, by the Gods I swear she must have studied in a Mythran brothel."

    old "Really, Antonio, you don't have to-"
    new "Really, Antonio, you don't have to-"

    old "Share? I know, I know, but I'm a nice person."
    new "Share? I know, I know, but I'm a nice person."

    old "If you want I can have the girl brought to your bed tonight?"
    new "If you want I can have the girl brought to your bed tonight?"

    old "I don't think that will be necessary."
    new "I don't think that will be necessary."

    old "Really, it's no big deal. I like to share with my friends. And we are friends, right?"
    new "Really, it's no big deal. I like to share with my friends. And we are friends, right?"

    old "Edmond sighed."
    new "Edmond sighed."

    old "Please, lets table all this talk for now."
    new "Please, lets table all this talk for now."

    old "Focus on serious matters."
    new "Focus on serious matters."

    old "Antonio nodded."
    new "Antonio nodded."

    old "Of course, business before pleasure."
    new "Of course, business before pleasure."

    old "But if you had seen this girl's ass, I swear you would have-"
    new "But if you had seen this girl's ass, I swear you would have-"

    old "Edmond bashed the table with his fist."
    new "Edmond bashed the table with his fist."

    old "Sarah could see Duke Antonio appeared genuine startled."
    new "Sarah could see Duke Antonio appeared genuine startled."

    old "Fine, fine. Apologies, my friend."
    new "Fine, fine. Apologies, my friend."

    old "Best we table this, now that ladies are present."
    new "Best we table this, now that ladies are present."

    old "Sarah bowed, grateful to be acknowledged and for the talk of the servant girl to be over with."
    new "Sarah bowed, grateful to be acknowledged and for the talk of the servant girl to be over with."

    old "She took her place opposite the two men."
    new "She took her place opposite the two men."

    old "I pray you each had a good night at the feast."
    new "I pray you each had a good night at the feast."

    old "Antonio began to grin again."
    new "Antonio began to grin again."

    old "Most fine indeed."
    new "Most fine indeed."

    old "I endured."
    new "I endured."

    old "My head is still pounding. Speaking of pounding-"
    new "My head is still pounding. Speaking of pounding-"

    old "The door opened and Queen Maeiv entered."
    new "The door opened and Queen Maeiv entered."

    old "Everyone turned to her."
    new "Everyone turned to her."

    old "I am glad to see you are all here."
    new "I am glad to see you are all here."

    old "Sarah noticed the way she carried herself."
    new "Sarah noticed the way she carried herself."

    old "From her own experience of ruling, Sarah knew that every ruler, to some degree, played a role."
    new "From her own experience of ruling, Sarah knew that every ruler, to some degree, played a role."

    old "Maeiv, for her part, played it perfectly."
    new "Maeiv, for her part, played it perfectly."

    old "Every part of her crafted to perfection. Every slight movement, even those that pretended to be natural, practiced and perfect."
    new "Every part of her crafted to perfection. Every slight movement, even those that pretended to be natural, practiced and perfect."

    old "She took her seat next to Sarah."
    new "She took her seat next to Sarah."

    old "For a moment, the room was silent, waiting for her next word."
    new "For a moment, the room was silent, waiting for her next word."

    old "Allow me to begin by apologizing."
    new "Allow me to begin by apologizing."

    old "Sarah frowned. She had not expected that."
    new "Sarah frowned. She had not expected that."

    old "I have invited each of you here, but I am well aware that I have not been as forthright as I should have been."
    new "I have invited each of you here, but I am well aware that I have not been as forthright as I should have been."

    old "I offered you an invitation to this Union Council, and little more."
    new "I offered you an invitation to this Union Council, and little more."

    old "Duke Antonio chuckled."
    new "Duke Antonio chuckled."

    old "I half considered not attending at all, were it not for my curiosity."
    new "I half considered not attending at all, were it not for my curiosity."

    old "Queen Maeiv gracefully nodded."
    new "Queen Maeiv gracefully nodded."

    old "And I am grateful that you did, Duke Antonio, for the matter we must discuss is of grave importance."
    new "And I am grateful that you did, Duke Antonio, for the matter we must discuss is of grave importance."

    old "Marshal Edmond leaned forward."
    new "Marshal Edmond leaned forward."

    old "Of importance to whom?"
    new "Of importance to whom?"

    old "All of us."
    new "All of us."

    old "Again, the others went silent."
    new "Again, the others went silent."

    old "Sarah for her part considered. Observed. She would speak when she knew the play that was unfolding."
    new "Sarah for her part considered. Observed. She would speak when she knew the play that was unfolding."

    old "My great city of Delphine is home to not just great artisans."
    new "My great city of Delphine is home to not just great artisans."

    old "In regarding to some particular fields, such as wines and jewelcrafting, the talents of our artisans are unrivaled."
    new "In regarding to some particular fields, such as wines and jewelcrafting, the talents of our artisans are unrivaled."

    old "This has meant that my nation has always held deeper ties to the rest of the world."
    new "This has meant that my nation has always held deeper ties to the rest of the world."

    old "Drawn in by the unique talent of our craftsmen, we see visitors from every edge of the world."
    new "Drawn in by the unique talent of our craftsmen, we see visitors from every edge of the world."

    old "She paused for a moment."
    new "She paused for a moment."

    old "This also means that our need for information regarding these partners from across the world, has been more vital to us than others in the Union."
    new "This also means that our need for information regarding these partners from across the world, has been more vital to us than others in the Union."

    old "Our spy network, as a result, runs deeper and wider than any of yours. Perhaps even more than all of yours together."
    new "Our spy network, as a result, runs deeper and wider than any of yours. Perhaps even more than all of yours together."

    old "This is not a matter of bragging. For us, it is a fact that is necessary to our survival."
    new "This is not a matter of bragging. For us, it is a fact that is necessary to our survival."

    old "Queen Maeiv leaned forward and placed a piece of parchment on the table."
    new "Queen Maeiv leaned forward and placed a piece of parchment on the table."

    old "Pictured on it, a map of the Union Kingdoms, detailed lines, numbers, and a language that Sarah could not read but easily recognized for its distinct shapes."
    new "Pictured on it, a map of the Union Kingdoms, detailed lines, numbers, and a language that Sarah could not read but easily recognized for its distinct shapes."

    old "Mythran script."
    new "Mythran script."

    old "What is this?"
    new "What is this?"

    old "My spies uncovered this document nearly a year ago."
    new "My spies uncovered this document nearly a year ago."

    old "The source, though I cannot disclose it, is a very high placed asset in the Mythran empire."
    new "The source, though I cannot disclose it, is a very high placed asset in the Mythran empire."

    old "It came directly from the Eternal Court itself."
    new "It came directly from the Eternal Court itself."

    old "The Eternal Court, the nexus of power where all the rulers of the Mythran Empire gathered in one place."
    new "The Eternal Court, the nexus of power where all the rulers of the Mythran Empire gathered in one place."

    old "She tapped the document."
    new "She tapped the document."

    old "Starting from the discovery of this document, we began to continue our investigation and we uncovered further supporting evidence."
    new "Starting from the discovery of this document, we began to continue our investigation and we uncovered further supporting evidence."

    old "You still haven't told us what this is, exactly."
    new "You still haven't told us what this is, exactly."

    old "Maeiv smiled."
    new "Maeiv smiled."

    old "Quite right."
    new "Quite right."

    old "She tapped the map again."
    new "She tapped the map again."

    old "This is a map for a proposed invasion of the Union Kingdoms by several Mythran Legions."
    new "This is a map for a proposed invasion of the Union Kingdoms by several Mythran Legions."

    old "Duke Antonio leaned back."
    new "Duke Antonio leaned back."

    old "That is what this is about?"
    new "That is what this is about?"

    old "It does not concern you?"
    new "It does not concern you?"

    old "Duke Antonio laughed."
    new "Duke Antonio laughed."

    old "Please."
    new "Please."

    old "The threat of a Mythran invasion of our lands is a joke."
    new "The threat of a Mythran invasion of our lands is a joke."

    old "I remember being a little boy, playing at my grandfather's feet, and they whispered the same rumors."
    new "I remember being a little boy, playing at my grandfather's feet, and they whispered the same rumors."

    old "And it's always that. Rumors. Forever threatening, never happening."
    new "And it's always that. Rumors. Forever threatening, never happening."

    old "Queen Maeiv leaned forward."
    new "Queen Maeiv leaned forward."

    old "It is different this time."
    new "It is different this time."

    old "This time the threat is real."
    new "This time the threat is real."

    old "How? What has changed?"
    new "How? What has changed?"

    old "We are still too unimportant for them to bother with, yet too tough to start a war with."
    new "We are still too unimportant for them to bother with, yet too tough to start a war with."

    old "They make a hundred times more in trade with us than they could ever hope to loot."
    new "They make a hundred times more in trade with us than they could ever hope to loot."

    old "Maeiv leaned back."
    new "Maeiv leaned back."

    old "Because this cause now has a champion. Someone who is obsessively pushing the notion within the Eternal Court."
    new "Because this cause now has a champion. Someone who is obsessively pushing the notion within the Eternal Court."

    old "And he has gained the authorization to deploy two legions."
    new "And he has gained the authorization to deploy two legions."

    old "He is a Noctori, by the name of Gilead."
    new "He is a Noctori, by the name of Gilead."

    old "Noctorio were the ruling elite that lived within the Eternal Court."
    new "Noctorio were the ruling elite that lived within the Eternal Court."

    old "Blessed with exceedingly long lifespans, most were some three centuries old."
    new "Blessed with exceedingly long lifespans, most were some three centuries old."

    old "The origin of their long lives was unkown, even within the Empire itself, and a secret they intended to keep above all."
    new "The origin of their long lives was unkown, even within the Empire itself, and a secret they intended to keep above all."

    old "It was in part this steady, long lasting rule, that have given the Mythran Empire its stability."
    new "It was in part this steady, long lasting rule, that have given the Mythran Empire its stability."

    old "Gilead?"
    new "Gilead?"

    old "He is an older Noctori, who gained his fame in the Mythran campaigns against the Orcish hordes."
    new "He is an older Noctori, who gained his fame in the Mythran campaigns against the Orcish hordes."

    old "Though his standing has faded, his reputation among the Eternal Court remains significant."
    new "Though his standing has faded, his reputation among the Eternal Court remains significant."

    old "He has spend these last few years preparing, pushing for this exact invasion."
    new "He has spend these last few years preparing, pushing for this exact invasion."

    old "With the confirmation that he has been granted two legions, there is now nothing that will stop him from carrying out his plans."
    new "With the confirmation that he has been granted two legions, there is now nothing that will stop him from carrying out his plans."

    old "But why?"
    new "But why?"

    old "Why would they attack us now?"
    new "Why would they attack us now?"

    old "As Duke Antonio mentioned, the conditions have not changed from before. They stand to gain little, and pay a hefty price."
    new "As Duke Antonio mentioned, the conditions have not changed from before. They stand to gain little, and pay a hefty price."

    old "Why would the Mythrans be so foolish?"
    new "Why would the Mythrans be so foolish?"

    old "Maeiv leaned on the arm of her chair."
    new "Maeiv leaned on the arm of her chair."

    old "I cannot say."
    new "I cannot say."

    old "My spies know of the attack plans. They uncovered the authorization for the use of two legions. We also have significant supporting evidence."
    new "My spies know of the attack plans. They uncovered the authorization for the use of two legions. We also have significant supporting evidence."

    old "But I cannot uncover his reasoning."
    new "But I cannot uncover his reasoning."

    old "Perhaps it is simply conquest for the sake of it? History is not unfamiliar with men who write their names in blood."
    new "Perhaps it is simply conquest for the sake of it? History is not unfamiliar with men who write their names in blood."

    old "You might be right, Lord Edmond, but I cannot speak to it with certainty."
    new "You might be right, Lord Edmond, but I cannot speak to it with certainty."

    old "Duke Antonio frowned."
    new "Duke Antonio frowned."

    old "So we go home, prepare our armies, send out diplomats. Pray for peace. Maybe pay them a tribute to make them reconsider?"
    new "So we go home, prepare our armies, send out diplomats. Pray for peace. Maybe pay them a tribute to make them reconsider?"

    old "Maeiv shook her head."
    new "Maeiv shook her head."

    old "I wish that could be the solution, but this brings me to the final discovery made by my spies."
    new "I wish that could be the solution, but this brings me to the final discovery made by my spies."

    old "She placed a document on the table. More Mythran script. A letter."
    new "She placed a document on the table. More Mythran script. A letter."

    old "This document outlines their strategy for attacking the Union."
    new "This document outlines their strategy for attacking the Union."

    old "I can't read their gibberish, what does it say?"
    new "I can't read their gibberish, what does it say?"

    old "You really can't read Mythran? You people from Elarand really are savages."
    new "You really can't read Mythran? You people from Elarand really are savages."

    old "Sarah watched Duke Antonio read. His face slowly frowning."
    new "Sarah watched Duke Antonio read. His face slowly frowning."

    old "I see..."
    new "I see..."

    old "Frustrated at being left out, Edmond leaned forward."
    new "Frustrated at being left out, Edmond leaned forward."

    old "Tell me, what does it say."
    new "Tell me, what does it say."

    old "Their strategy revolves around splitting us apart."
    new "Their strategy revolves around splitting us apart."

    old "They identify, correctly, that the Union Kingdoms are fragmented and easily turned against one another."
    new "They identify, correctly, that the Union Kingdoms are fragmented and easily turned against one another."

    old "They hope to threaten each of us, and in turn, hope that one of us will strike a bargain with them."
    new "They hope to threaten each of us, and in turn, hope that one of us will strike a bargain with them."

    old "And why would we do that?"
    new "And why would we do that?"

    old "Because each of us distrusts the other."
    new "Because each of us distrusts the other."

    old "Queen Maeiv smiled."
    new "Queen Maeiv smiled."

    old "Each of us fears that the offer of working with the Mythrans might also be given to another."
    new "Each of us fears that the offer of working with the Mythrans might also be given to another."

    old "So they hope one of us will agree, if not because of strategy, then out of fear that one of the other's would take the offer."
    new "So they hope one of us will agree, if not because of strategy, then out of fear that one of the other's would take the offer."

    old "Exactly. They will play us against one another."
    new "Exactly. They will play us against one another."

    old "And the reason I have gathered you here, is because I know they are right. Their plan will work."
    new "And the reason I have gathered you here, is because I know they are right. Their plan will work."

    old "Edmond groaned."
    new "Edmond groaned."

    old "Work with these foreign dogs? Never."
    new "Work with these foreign dogs? Never."

    old "And would you say the same of Duke Antonio? Do you suspect he would also never work with them?"
    new "And would you say the same of Duke Antonio? Do you suspect he would also never work with them?"

    old "Edmond looked at the Duke with distaste."
    new "Edmond looked at the Duke with distaste."

    old "Those Medini have always valued coin over integrity. If the price is right, he'd probably sell them his mother."
    new "Those Medini have always valued coin over integrity. If the price is right, he'd probably sell them his mother."

    old "Absurd!"
    new "Absurd!"

    old "Duke Antonio leaned forward, animated."
    new "Duke Antonio leaned forward, animated."

    old "I won't need to sit here and have my loyalty questioned by some usurper."
    new "I won't need to sit here and have my loyalty questioned by some usurper."

    old "Watch how you speak to me, fat man!"
    new "Watch how you speak to me, fat man!"

    old "Queen Maeiv slapped her open palm on the table. The loud bang silenced the room."
    new "Queen Maeiv slapped her open palm on the table. The loud bang silenced the room."

    old "There you have it."
    new "There you have it."

    old "They won't have to divide us. We're already divided."
    new "They won't have to divide us. We're already divided."

    old "Sarah nodded in agreement."
    new "Sarah nodded in agreement."

    old "They will land on our shores and pick us off one by one. Each of us will retreat behind our walls, and we will let the others to themselves."
    new "They will land on our shores and pick us off one by one. Each of us will retreat behind our walls, and we will let the others to themselves."

    old "The Mythrans rely on this, because they know a united Union would be too much for their two legions."
    new "The Mythrans rely on this, because they know a united Union would be too much for their two legions."

    old "But divided, they will slowly carve us up and turn us into vassals."
    new "But divided, they will slowly carve us up and turn us into vassals."

    old "So what then? What options do we have? The Mythran Empire is the most powerful force in the known world."
    new "So what then? What options do we have? The Mythran Empire is the most powerful force in the known world."

    old "We must come together."
    new "We must come together."

    old "We must reform the Union, and put into place a Union King...or Queen."
    new "We must reform the Union, and put into place a Union King...or Queen."

    old "The room went silent."
    new "The room went silent."

    old "Each considered the notion. Ceding power, abhorent."
    new "Each considered the notion. Ceding power, abhorent."

    old "Then each reconsidered the notion, and imagined themselves at the head of such a Union."
    new "Then each reconsidered the notion, and imagined themselves at the head of such a Union."

    old "Our nations are fragmented. We have been for centuries...the task you speak of..."
    new "Our nations are fragmented. We have been for centuries...the task you speak of..."

    old "Is enormous."
    new "Is enormous."

    old "I am well aware."
    new "I am well aware."

    old "And was it not for this threat, I would never have considered it."
    new "And was it not for this threat, I would never have considered it."

    old "But the truth is that we must, or we will all be destroyed, one by one."
    new "But the truth is that we must, or we will all be destroyed, one by one."

    old "I see, and so the purpose of this council would then be to decide on who rules over such a Union."
    new "I see, and so the purpose of this council would then be to decide on who rules over such a Union."

    old "Queen Maeiv nodded."
    new "Queen Maeiv nodded."

    old "That, as well as deciding on what such a Union would look like."
    new "That, as well as deciding on what such a Union would look like."

    old "To come together we must do more than simply write it on paper. We will have to alter the laws. Reshape our armies."
    new "To come together we must do more than simply write it on paper. We will have to alter the laws. Reshape our armies."

    old "The task is great, and in any other circumstance would take years."
    new "The task is great, and in any other circumstance would take years."

    old "I fear we have only weeks."
    new "I fear we have only weeks."

    old "Weeks to decide, perhaps only months to implement these changes before the attack comes."
    new "Weeks to decide, perhaps only months to implement these changes before the attack comes."

    old "Sarah frowned. So much work. With such conflicting interests."
    new "Sarah frowned. So much work. With such conflicting interests."

    old "And what if I say to hell with it?"
    new "And what if I say to hell with it?"

    old "Queen Maeiv shrugged."
    new "Queen Maeiv shrugged."

    old "We are all peers. I cannot force any of you to do as I ask."
    new "We are all peers. I cannot force any of you to do as I ask."

    old "Either we overcome our differences and reform the Union and elect a leader, or we fail to do so and face the consequences."
    new "Either we overcome our differences and reform the Union and elect a leader, or we fail to do so and face the consequences."

    old "If any of you wish to withdraw, simply say so and we can be done with the matter."
    new "If any of you wish to withdraw, simply say so and we can be done with the matter."

    old "And I can rest knowing I did all that I could to convince you of the right path."
    new "And I can rest knowing I did all that I could to convince you of the right path."

    old "The room was silent."
    new "The room was silent."

    old "None motioned to leave."
    new "None motioned to leave."

    old "I will stay. At the very least to hear you all out. Discuss. See more of this evidence."
    new "I will stay. At the very least to hear you all out. Discuss. See more of this evidence."

    old "Duke Antonio nodded along with her."
    new "Duke Antonio nodded along with her."

    old "Well if the girl can find it in herself to stay, then I'd be a mighty coward if I was the one to walk away."
    new "Well if the girl can find it in herself to stay, then I'd be a mighty coward if I was the one to walk away."

    old "Queen Maeiv looked at Edmond, the most hestitant, the last one to speak."
    new "Queen Maeiv looked at Edmond, the most hestitant, the last one to speak."

    old "What of you, Lord Edmond?"
    new "What of you, Lord Edmond?"

    old "Marshal Edmond groaned. With any other man, such a noise meant a no. For him, it meant a pained yes."
    new "Marshal Edmond groaned. With any other man, such a noise meant a no. For him, it meant a pained yes."

    old "Very well, let it not be said when this all collapses on top of us, that I was to be blamed."
    new "Very well, let it not be said when this all collapses on top of us, that I was to be blamed."

    old "Excellent, then we have an agreement."
    new "Excellent, then we have an agreement."

    old "I shall provided each of you with all that my spies have gathered."
    new "I shall provided each of you with all that my spies have gathered."

    old "In the coming weeks we can discuss our differences and hopefully resolve them."
    new "In the coming weeks we can discuss our differences and hopefully resolve them."

    old "If we succeed, we shall be the rulers that re-establish the Union, after centuries of fragmentation."
    new "If we succeed, we shall be the rulers that re-establish the Union, after centuries of fragmentation."

    old "Sarah could feel her heart beat faster. She'd be lying if she said the notion was not interesting to her."
    new "Sarah could feel her heart beat faster. She'd be lying if she said the notion was not interesting to her."

    old "For now, I will give each of you time to consider and reflect."
    new "For now, I will give each of you time to consider and reflect."

    old "Your rooms, of course, are yours to use for the remainder of your stay."
    new "Your rooms, of course, are yours to use for the remainder of your stay."

    old "When she came back to her room, Sarah processed all that she had heard from Queen Maeiv."
    new "When she came back to her room, Sarah processed all that she had heard from Queen Maeiv."

    old "Later, crates full of documents began to arrive at her room. The sum total of the information of Maeiv's spy network."
    new "Later, crates full of documents began to arrive at her room. The sum total of the information of Maeiv's spy network."

    old "On top of all the gathered information, an endless series of policy proposals, big and small."
    new "On top of all the gathered information, an endless series of policy proposals, big and small."

    old "Among them, a single large red folder contained the most pressing issue of all."
    new "Among them, a single large red folder contained the most pressing issue of all."

    old "A proposal on how to organize the Union Kingdom's armies, should they unify."
    new "A proposal on how to organize the Union Kingdom's armies, should they unify."

    old "The kingdoms were far from equal in terms of their military."
    new "The kingdoms were far from equal in terms of their military."

    old "Rosanna itself had one of the strongest armies, being the only nation flanked by the Tribes of the desert."
    new "Rosanna itself had one of the strongest armies, being the only nation flanked by the Tribes of the desert."

    old "Medini itself had the weakest army, instead prefering to call on their vast network of mercenaries when needed."
    new "Medini itself had the weakest army, instead prefering to call on their vast network of mercenaries when needed."

    old "Elarand itself had the largest population, and thus the largest potential army."
    new "Elarand itself had the largest population, and thus the largest potential army."

    old "But the succession of internal conflicts and coups had left their army in a weakend state for the time."
    new "But the succession of internal conflicts and coups had left their army in a weakend state for the time."

    old "Finally, Normandi itself had a balanced army. Perhaps smallest out of all the nations, but experienced and professional."
    new "Finally, Normandi itself had a balanced army. Perhaps smallest out of all the nations, but experienced and professional."

    old "Given the country's small size, the army was more than capable of defending itself from any regional rivals."
    new "Given the country's small size, the army was more than capable of defending itself from any regional rivals."

    old "Sarah began to consider her next move."
    new "Sarah began to consider her next move."

    old "Mainting seperate armies would be a way for herself to hold onto more power, given that hers was the strongest singular army."
    new "Mainting seperate armies would be a way for herself to hold onto more power, given that hers was the strongest singular army."

